Company description: Fincantieri is one of the world’s largest shipbuilding groups and number one by diversification and innovation. It is leader in cruise ship design and construction and a reference player in all high-tech shipbuilding industry’s sectors, from naval to offshore vessels, from high-complexity special vessels and ferries to mega-yachts, ship repairs and conversions, systems and components production and after-sales services. Headquartered in Trieste (Italy), the Group has built more than 7,000 vessels in over 230 years of maritime history. With almost 20,000 employees, of whom more than 7,800 in Italy, 20 shipyards in 4 continents, today Fincantieri is the leading Western shipbuilder. It has among its clients the major cruise operators, the Italian and the U.S. Navy, in addition to several foreign navies, and it is partner of some of the main European defense companies within supranational programmes.

Company description: Stena AB is a diversified Swedish company headquartered in Göteborg, operating across multiple sectors, including shipping, ferry services, offshore drilling, property management, and finance. With a mission to create sustainable value, Stena emphasizes care, innovation, and effective performance, aiming to be the first choice for its customers while contributing positively to society and the environment. The company operates a fleet of 131 vessels and manages over 29,300 residential and commercial units, catering to a diverse clientele that ranges from individual consumers to large corporations. Stena's vision is centered on safeguarding resources and fostering long-term relationships with customers and partners, reflecting its commitment to responsible business practices and social development. Stena's subsidiaries, such as Stena Line and Stena Bulk, play significant roles in their respective markets, with Stena Bulk recognized as a leading tanker shipping company specializing in the transportation of crude oil, refined products, and chemicals. The company is dedicated to promoting sustainable shipping practices, focusing on the development of hybrid vessels and alternative fuels to minimize environmental impact. Stena collaborates with industry leaders and invests in innovative technologies, including AI and sustainable fuels, to enhance efficiency and reduce carbon emissions. With approximately 18,000 employees worldwide, Stena is committed to continuous improvement and sustainability, adapting to changing market conditions while maintaining high standards of service and operational excellence. The company serves a wide range of clients, including major players in the maritime and energy sectors, and actively engages in partnerships that promote local workforce development and community engagement. Stena's ethical practices, including a zero-tolerance policy for corruption and a focus on human rights, ensure that its business activities contribute positively to society. Through its commitment to achieving net-zero emissions by 2050, Stena AB aims to lead in its industries while creating long-term value for both customers and society.

Company description: Stena Line is one of the largest ferry companies in the world, operating a fleet of approximately 40 vessels across 20 routes in Northern Europe and the Mediterranean. Founded in 1962 and headquartered in Gothenburg, Sweden, the company is dedicated to connecting Europe for a sustainable future by providing reliable transport solutions for both passengers and freight. Stena Line's mission emphasizes the importance of caring for the planet, people, and business, striving to minimize its environmental impact while ensuring safe and efficient operations. The company serves a diverse clientele, including leisure travelers, commercial freight customers, and business partners, and collaborates with various stakeholders to enhance intermodal transport solutions. With a workforce of over 6,300 employees, Stena Line fosters a culture of teamwork and inclusivity, continuously working towards improving its services and sustainability initiatives. The company specializes in providing efficient and sustainable transportation services across key routes, primarily connecting the UK, Ireland, and continental Europe. Stena Line's vision focuses on being the preferred choice for ferry travel, leveraging innovative solutions to enhance service offerings and reduce carbon emissions. Stena Line is committed to delivering high-quality travel experiences while prioritizing sustainability, as evidenced by their initiatives such as sourcing certified seafood, offering plant-based dining options, and minimizing food waste through innovative practices. The company collaborates with local tourism boards and logistics partners to promote regional tourism and economic growth, targeting both individual travelers and businesses seeking reliable transport options. With a strong focus on innovation and environmental responsibility, Stena Line aims to lead the way in sustainable ferry transportation, ensuring that it meets the evolving needs of its customers while contributing to a greener maritime industry.

Company description: Irish Continental Group Plc engages in the provision of logistic management services. The company is headquartered in Dublin, Dublin and currently employs 282 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2014-06-10. The firm carries passengers and cars, Roll on Roll off (RoRo) freight and Container Lift on Lift off (LoLo) freight, on routes between Ireland, Britain and Continental Europe. The firm also operates container terminals in the ports of Dublin and Belfast. The Group operates through two divisions: the Ferries Division, whose principal activities include passenger and RoRo freight shipping services under the Irish Ferries brand together with ship chartering activities, and the Container and Terminal Division, whose principal activities include LoLo shipping activities under the Eucon brand and the operation of two container terminals, Dublin Ferryport Terminals (DFT) and Belfast Container Terminal (BCT), within the two main ports on the island of Ireland. Container shipping provides full door-to-door container transport service between Ireland and approximately 20 European countries.

The company aims to enhance the travel experience for its customers through initiatives such as the Baleària Club loyalty program, which rewards members with points and exclusive benefits. Its target market includes both leisure travelers and businesses that require reliable cargo transport, ensuring that it meets the diverse needs of its clientele. Baleària prides itself on its punctuality, the digitalization of services, and a strong commitment to customer satisfaction, making it a trusted choice for maritime travel. With a focus on providing efficient and eco-friendly services, Baleària caters to a wide range of customers, including tourists, local residents, and businesses. Company description: Viking Line is a leading maritime transport company based in Åland, specializing in passenger and freight ferry services across the northern Baltic Sea, particularly connecting Finland, Sweden, and Estonia. With a strong focus on sustainability, Viking Line is dedicated to promoting responsible tourism practices and protecting the delicate ecosystems of the Baltic Sea. As Finland's largest maritime employer, Viking Line prioritizes employee welfare and engagement, fostering a positive working environment through collective bargaining agreements. The company aims to maintain its market leadership while adapting to evolving environmental regulations and market demands. By continuously innovating and enhancing its services, Viking Line strives to exceed customer expectations and contribute positively to the communities it operates within, solidifying its position as a key player in the regional transportation market.

Established with a commitment to enhancing the travel experience for island residents and visitors, the company actively engages with local communities through customer panels initiated in 2008. These panels, composed of representatives from various local organizations and residents, meet regularly to evaluate and improve the company's services based on community feedback. Company description: PKP CARGO CONNECT is an international logistics operator providing comprehensive services in the field of transport, reloading, loading and customs services. Extensive experience enables the implementation of complex forwarding projects in the country and abroad. Company description: Wagenborg is een onderdeel van het familiebedrijf Royal Wagenborg, waarvan het hoofdkantoor in Delfzijl is gevestigd. Jaarlijks vervoeren wij met onze veerboten, watertaxi's en sneldienst ruim 1,5 miljoen passagiers en zo’n 200.000 auto's en vrachtauto’s. Een ambitieuze veerdienst die al meer dan een eeuw ieder seizoen passagiers van en naar de Waddeneilanden Ameland en Schiermonnikoog vervoert. En dat in een ongeëvenaard dynamisch natuurgebied. Veilig en verantwoord varen op Werelderfgoed de Waddenzee met respect voor de natuur. Dat zien we terug in alles: in ons beleid, in onze werkwijze en in onze medewerkers die graag de handen uit de mouwen steken. In april 2014 heeft de Minister van Infrastructuur en Milieu aan Wagenborg Passagiersdiensten voor de looptijd van 15 jaar de Concessie Waddenveren Oost verleend. Al met al zijn wij al ruim een eeuw een betrouwbare partner van de overheid. Ook na 2029 willen wij de concessie graag behouden. Daarom leggen wij de lat steeds een beetje hoger als het gaat om het niveau van service, kwaliteit, veiligheid en klantentevredenheid. Wij willen dat onze passagiers zich prettig voelen aan boord en varen met eersteklas materiaal. Veiligheid, kwaliteit en continuïteit staan voorop. Daar kunnen onze reizigers en medewerkers op rekenen.

Company description: Spółka Unity Line, założona w maju 1994 roku jest jedną z największych firm armatorskich działających na rynku bałtyckich przewozów promowych, wchodzi w skład grupy kapitałowej Polskiej Żeglugi Morskiej (PŻM). W ramach prowadzonej działalności firma zajmuje się profesjonalnym zarządzaniem promami morskimi oraz działalnością turystyczną i transportową. Struktura floty Unity Line umożliwia obsługę wszystkich grup odbiorców: pasażerów, spedytorów oraz przewoźników drogowych i kolejowych. Promy w zarządzie Spółki eksploatowane są na liniach: Świnoujście – Ystad oraz Świnoujście – Trelleborg. Za wizytówkę Unity Line uważany jest prom Polonia. Jednostka oddana do eksploatacji w 1995 roku, nadal uchodzi za jeden z nowocześniejszych i najbezpieczniejszych promów pływających po wodach Bałtyku. Rosnące zainteresowanie usługami Unity Line oraz stały rozwój oferty w bezpośredni sposób przekładają się na kolejne inwestycje podejmowane przez Spółkę. We wrześniu 2008 roku, do ruchu wprowadzona została kolejna jednostka pasażerska – m/f Skania. Dzięki temu promy pasażerskie Unity Line pokonują trasę Świnoujście – Ystad w ruchu wahadłowym. Oznacza to, że pasażerowie w jeszcze bardziej elastyczny i komfortowy sposób mogą planować swoją podróż. Obok jednostek pasażerskich – promów Polonia i Skania – w zarządzie Unity Line znajduje się pięć jednostek zorientowanych na obsługę rynku cargo – prom ładunkowy: Copernicus; promy ładunkowo-pasażerskie: Gryf, Galileusz, Wolin i Epsilon.

Company description: Levante Ferries Group, combining the noble aspects of Hellenic Naval Tradition with the modern spirit of new technologies and concepts, quickly established itself in the service of the Patras - Kyllini - Zakynthos - Kefalonia - Ithaca sea area, offering to the Passenger modern ships, as well as advanced land services. "Key" factor in the rapid development of Levante Ferries and its consolidation in passenger consciousness was the significant experience of its executives in serving citizens-passengers, as well as its pioneering approach to the evolution of the Ferry - Shipping market and the needs of the travelers in the Ionian Sea. The Levante Ferries fleet consists of four ships built to the highest standards: the brand new «Fior di Levante», the beautiful «Mare di Levante», the modernized «Andreas Kalvos» and the well-known «Kefalonia». Our ships, staffed with experienced and fully trained crews, offer passengers a completely safe, comfortable and pleasant trip, even in the toughest weather conditions. Levante Ferries has also made possible for passengers to issue an e-ticket, supported by a smartphone app, thus making queues a thing of the past. Levante Ferries, despite the warm welcome of travelers, does not rest, but closely monitors every modern technology and up-to-date specification, aiming to be present in the "next day" developments of the Ferry - Shipping market with a structured strategy and an organized plan, that lead to a stronger fleet, even more routes and new destinations. Levante Ferries' central vision is to bring “the Ionian Sea Forward” and its ferry -shipping services to become a model in the Greek and international markets. Our Company recognizes its responsibility as a universal service provider and pledges not to rest until its will for "not even one blocked islander in the Ionian Sea" becomes reality.

Company description: Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. was founded in 1997 by the Venice Port Authority in order to manage and improve cruise traffic in the Port of Venice. The Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A.  operates in the Marittima and S. Basilio areas which stretch over a surface altogether of more than 244.000 sq. m. of which the Terminals occupy  53.000 sq. m. The maritime basin in the Marittima area measures circa 123.700 sq.m.   The shareholders of Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. are the following: APV Investimenti S.p.A., Finpax S.r.l., SAVE S.p.A. (Venice Marco Polo Airport), Veneto Sviluppo S.p.A., the Venice Chamber of Commerce  and the Venice Municipality. In addition Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. is the majority shareholder of two specialized companies: Venice Yacht Pier S.r.l. (V.Y.P.) founded to increase yachting in Venice and Venice Yachts and Ship Assistance (V.Y.S.A.) dedicated to the promotion of services for the maxi-yachts market. The growing needs of cruise traffic and Venice's appeal as a cultural and tourist attraction have given rise to the radical transformation of the Port area starting from 1997 as a result of the joint effort of Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. and the Venice Port Authority. Such transformation is exemplified by the renovation of ancient port buildings once dedicated to the commercial traffic, which have now become modern and multi-purpose facilities. Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A.'s port facilities cater the needs of any ship berthing in Venice.  ·          The Ferry Terminal 123 assists ferries for the Eastern Mediterranean area  ·          The S. Basilio Terminal accommodates medium-size cruise ships, mega-yachts and high speed hydrofoils  ·          Cruise Terminals 103, 107/108, 117 and Terminal Isonzo in the Marittima area are multi-purpose facilities which, additionally to their original purpose, are utilised for hosting meetings, conventions and fairs.

Company description: The Port of Hirtshals is an multimodal logistics centre situated in the heart of Scandinavia. The Danish port is the northernmost port on the European Westcoast, and many Norwegians refer to it as ‘the southernmost port in Norway’.  The Port of Hirtshals’ geographical position is a competitive strength. With the port’s location, directly to the North Sea, and only a short distance to one of the world’s busiest sea lanes, the possibilities of developing transport solutions are numerous.  The Port of Hirtshals has more than 60 ferries and ro/ro calls per week, and the port has services to five destinations in Norway, and services to the Faroe Island, Iceland, Russia, and Scotland: •	Bergen, Norway  •	Stavanger, Norway  •	Kristiansand, Norway  •	Langesund, Norway  •	Larvik, Norway  •	Torshavn, Faroe Islands  •	Seydisfjordur, Iceland  •	Reykjavik (Thorlakshöfn), Iceland •	Scrabster, Scotland The Port of Hirtshals is directly connected to the European motorway network. Motorway E39/E45 takes its starting point at the Port of Hirtshals, and continues to the German border and from there to the rest of Europe.  In 2015, a new combi terminal for rail traffic was established next to the port. Scheduled rail traffic has not yet been established, but more leading European rail operators are planning to start-up of traffic between Hirtshals and logistics centres in Europe.  In 2019, more than 150,000 trucks and trailers passed through the Port of Hirtshals, and approximately 20 % of these were craneable. The number of units and the increasing cargo traffic at the Port of Hirtshals underlines the potential for rail traffic between Hirtshals and Europe.  To obtain the benefits of combined transport in the transport sector, cooperation from all parties is essential.

Nowhere Networks is a Swedish high-tech company building the world’s most powerful land-based maritime broadband network. We deliver fast, reliable, and cost-effective internet connectivity to ferries, cruise ships, and cargo vessels - across Europe and expanding globally. But we’re not just a connectivity provider. We’re a full-stack operator. We design, build, install, and run everything ourselves. Whether it’s crew comms, passenger Wi-Fi, or real-time fleet operations, we make sure it all runs smoothly - and fast. We’re engineers, entrepreneurs, and problem-solvers who love building great tech and solving real-world challenges at sea. If you do too, come work with us.

Company description: Carus is a global supplier of information technology to the travel and transport industry.  We design, build and support systems critical to the operation and sales of ferry and cruise businesses around the world. Our objective is to take care of the full 360 degrees of the passenger journey.   Carus’ reservations system meets the demands of today’s fully digitalised ferry operations, providing mobile reservations, self-service check-in and boarding as well as digital cabin keys and lounge access control.   Carus’ onboard solution supports the management of all onboard services; fine-dining, bars, cafes, and retail. And our range of port automation solutions smooths the journey on approach to and within the port for foot-passengers, passenger vehicles as well as for cargo vehicles and units.   Carus’ clients operate throughout the Baltic, Europe, the United Kingdom, the United States, Africa, and Australia. Our clients represent every aspect of the passenger vessel industry and operate virtually every type of vessel, proving the versatility and flexibility of our solutions. Learn More: info@carus.com www.carus.com

Company description: Mammoet Ferry Transport was founded in 1983, a division of the heavy transport company ‘Mammoet Transport’, owned by Royal Dutch Nedlloyd. It was set up specifically to deal with Continent to UK haulage needs. Starting with two offices located in the Netherlands and England, the company later added subsidiaries in Belgium, Scotland, Germany, France and Austria. In July 2000 the heavy transport parent company ‘Mammoet Transport’ was sold by Nedlloyd to van Seumeren Holland. The ferry transport division was transferred into the hands of the Dutch management team through a management buy-out. Today Mammoet Ferry Transport BV operates with a staff of 80 highly motivated employees. Using a modern fleet of 400 trailers operating from seven subsidiaries, the company is confidently handling 30000 shipments annually. Activities The main activity of Mammoet Ferry Transport is the rapid transportation of freight from Continental Europe to the UK and vice versa, providing an effective transport link between industrial centers on both sides of the North Sea. Mammoet Ferry Transport offers a door-to-door operation, servicing Holland, Belgium, France, Germany, Austria, Luxembourg and the United Kingdom.

Company description: For the last 60 years, Stralsund based company Weiße Flotte has been operating day-trip and ferry services in the Federal State of Mecklenburg-West Pomerania jointly with its subsidiary Reederei Hiddensee.  Modern passenger vessels of the “Boddenkreuzer” type, a cargo ferry as well as fast water taxis make up the fleet that connects the two islands of Hiddensee and Rügen all year round. During the summer months, the timetable is supplemented with sailings from Stralsund, Wiek Dranske, Barth and Zingst. New or modernised passenger/ car vessels are deployed for ferry services in Warnemünde (Hohe Düne), Wittower Fähre (Rügen) and Stahlbrode – Glewitz (Rügen). A larger programme of harbour trips rounds off the products on offer.  Weiße Flotte and Reederei Hiddensee carry annually 3.4 million passengers and 846,000 vehicles.  The Weiße Flotte also operates a rowing boat ferry on behalf of the Berliner Verkehrsbetriebe (BVG) in Berlin. The group’s smallest vessel, the “Paule III”, entered service in 2015 and is able to transport 8 passengers or 4 passengers plus 4 bicycles.  Weiße Flotte  is one of the ventures of the FRS Förde Reederei Seetouristik, an internationally business group base in Northern Germany with a portfolio that comprises twenty-one subsidiaries located in Europe, North Africa and North America. In addition to numerous international ferry and catamaran lines, a shipmanagement company and the operation of a port complete the product range.

Established as a shipping company by local interests back in 1885, W.D.R. operates two year-round commuter ferry services linking Dagebüll with Wyk (Föhr Island) and Wittdün (Amrum Island) as well as Schlüttsiel with Hallig Hooge, Hallig Langeneß and Wittdün. Moreover, they constitute an essential basis for the region's prospering tourism industry. On an annual basis, W.D.R. records roughly 1.8 million passengers, 275,000 private cars and 36,000 trucks carried on its ferry services. Ferry operations form Wyker Dampfschiffs-Reederei's core business. Apart from that, the company operates one passenger excursion vessel, M/V "Rüm Hart", which is trading on day excursions from Wyk during summer.  Last but not least, the company operates public transportation on the islands of Föhr and Amrum: A fleet of 8 modern busses and coaches carry approximately 885,000 passengers annually.

Company description: During last 15 years, Naantali has become one of the most important Roro ports in Finland. Due to  the port´s significant investments in ferry traffic, the utilized cargo is increasing rapidly. Naantali is one of the largest Roro/Ropax port in Finland for trucks and trailers. Half of all truck and trailer transportations between Finland and Sweden are carried via Naantali by Ropax vessels.  The quick and fast sea route for cargo between Finland and Sweden. The Port of Naantali is an important link in the logistics chain of the Baltic Sea, which role is emphasized by its inclusion in the TEN-T traffic network, which covers the whole of Europe. The TEN-T core network links the Port of Naantali to both the Nordic Triangle and the Motorway of the Baltic Sea. The Port of Naantali is defined one of those four TEN-T core ports in Finland. Measured in tonnes of cargo, the Port of Naantali is one of the largest port in Finland. In recent years, total annual traffic at the Port of Naantali has averaged more than 7 million tonnes. With annual 1600 vessel calls the Port of Naantali is one of the most busiest ports. TEN-T core port with excellent logistical location on the European route 18 and well known Nordic triangle and Scandinavian-Mediterranean traffic corridor.  Naantali is long time known as a significant centre for dry bulk goods operations, thanks to excellent storage facilities and all-round value-added services.  Naantali is one of the largest ports eg. for grain and cement cargo handling in Finland. The port handles and stores also fertilizers, feed stuff and other other bulk materials as well as different type of recycling materials.  Currently Naantali offers several daily connections to Scandinavia with RoRo/Ropas vessels. There fast and regular connections ensure efficiency required by modern logistics and professional cargo transportation. Easy ice conditions. One of the deepest channels and quays in Finland.

Aegean Speed Lines was the first Greek company to employ a European Union flag vessel in the Greek cabotage, SPEEDRUNNER I, in the scope of deregulation of ferry services in our country. In 2006, Aegean Speed Lines changed its shareholders synthesis following the divestment of Sea Containers while the Eugenides Group of Companies maintained its significant share holding. This new scheme resulted from the synergy of well respected investors who consider Greek coastal shipping as a sector of the Greek Economy with high prospects. This new alliance provided Aegean Speed Lines with enhanced dynamics, feature at the needs of the modern passenger and the development of the islands. In the same respect, Aegean Speed Lines covers the transportation needs of the western Cycladic islands, because the company strongly believes that by offering a multitude of transportation solutions is catalytic to the growth and prosperity of all residents of the region. Staff of Aegean Speed Lines think and act as passengers themselves, so as to predict plans and offer on a daily basis, high standard services. Since 2009 till 2011, except the routes of Piraeus-Western Cyclades (Serifos, Sifnos, Milos, Kimolos, Folegandros), the fleet of Aegean Speed Lines served the Piraeus-Syros-Tinos-Mykonos, Piraeus-Thira-Ios - Sikinos and Piraeus-Paros-Naxos routes. In order to serve these schedules Aegean Speed Lines used three ultra-modern high-speed vessels: SPEEDRUNNER II, SPEEDRUNNER III, and SPEEDRUNNER IV which meet leading comfort, quality and safety requirements.  Just 5 years from its inception in December 2009, the company was granted the honours by Lloyds List, characterized as " The best shipping company of the year ", for its commitment and dedication to providing high quality services. Aegean Speed Lines has limited the schedule since 2015, attending to West Cyclades with SPEEDRUNNER III, which executes schedules to Piraeus - Serifos – Sifnos – Milos - Kimolos - Folegandros - Sikinos.

The European Union simply cannot function without its seaports. 90 % of Europe’s cargo trade in goods passes through the more than 1200 seaports existing in the 23 maritime Member States of the EU and more than 400 million passengers pass through Europe’s ports every year using ferry and cruise services. Without seaports, the European Union would not exist as an economic world power. Without seaports, there would be no internal market. ESPO ensures that seaports have a clear voice in the European Union. The organisation promotes the common interests of its members throughout Europe and is also engaged in dialogue with European stakeholders in the Port and Maritime sector. ESPO works through a permanent secretariat in Brussels, a General Assembly, an Executive Committee, and 8 specialised committees.

Company description: Deep Sea Pilots & Coastal Pilots The shipping lanes carrying global trade to- and from Europe’s main ports, come together and disperse at the entrance of the English Channel. This traffic is  funnelled into the Dover Strait from the North and the South. The narrow passage between France and the United Kingdom counts up to 500 shipping movements every day, ferries crossing the English channel not even taken into account.  Deep Sea Pilotage offers the best operational support and assistance for Masters, Officers, Owners and Shipmanagers to manage these risks in the dense North-European waters. With the extensive knowledge Deep Sea Pilots of Redwise – DCP, risks are brought down to an as low as reasonably practicable minimum. All Deep Sea Pilots of Redwise – DCP are highly experienced and certified. Vessel Traffic Services Deep Sea Pilots of Redwise – DCP are being deployed both voluntarily and mandatory in the capacity of Offshore VTS Pilots. A VTS Pilot can be placed on board pipe- and cable laying barges, offshore oil & gas platforms and survey vessels. With the knowledge and experience off navigating vessels through the North European waters, these experienced Pilots observe and guide the specific traffic safely in the vicinity of the projects. Observing the traffic around the projects 24/7, broadcasting safety information regularly and in-time intervention, prevents potentially dangerous situations. This provides added safety for the people working on projects, the environment and can prevent damage to materials, ships and structures. It significantly reduces the risk of down-time and major catastrophes. Company description: Aboa Mare offers Bachelor and Master level education at Novia UAS and secondary education at Axxell vocational institute. We educate Sea Captains, Marine Engineers, Watchkeeping Officers and Watchkeeping Engineers. Aboa Mare Training Center offers a wide range of courses both for professional seafarers and leisure-time boaters. In order to be able to offer a wide range of courses and satisfy the requirements of our clients, we have a large network of experts on diverse fields within seafaring. Today we have several international customers and we have a close co-operation with Wärtsilä and ABB which give us the knowledge of training international crews. Aboa Mare is STCW audited by the Finnish Transport Safety Agency. Part of our education is audited by the DNV ISO 9001 standard. Aboa Mare offers training in safety at sea and environmentally sustainable development issues related to seafaring. We focus on providing simulator-based training for maritime students, shipping companies, authorities including pilots and sea rescuers as well as for leisure boating. In the simulations we use different shipmodels, e.g. large cruise ships, tankers and smaller archipelago ferries. The simulations are conducted on Finnish coastal areas and lakes as well as on the most heavily trafficked routes worldwide. The simulation resources consist of 9 simulator bridges, engine room simulators, VTS simulator, DP simulator and radio simulator. We can offer training on Consilium, Furuno, Wärtsilä, Transas and Sperry Marine bridges in our simulator. With the simulator interface we have developed we can generate technical faults to the real navigational instruments on the bridges.

Company description: Een wandeling door een natuurgebied kan meer dan eens onderbroken worden door water. In veel gevallen is er dan een bemande voetveer om toeristen naar de overkant te brengen, maar dat komt steeds minder voor. Ferry Plan speelt hier op in en brengt u naar de overkant. Ferry Easy. Ferry Easy biedt uw passagiers (maximaal 12 voetgangers) een veilige en duurzame overtocht. Het minimalistische design van Ferry Easy, zorgt er tevens voor dat alleen noodzakelijke componenten op het voetveer aanwezig zijn. Hierdoor blijft Ferry Easy licht en dat bespaart weer energie. De stroom die Ferry Easy nodig heeft wordt opgewekt uit de zonnecellen op de overkapping. Daarnaast is Ferry Easy ook nog eens gemaakt van duurzaam aluminium. Aan wal staat aan iedere zijde een paal met een knop. De passagier drukt op de knop en Ferry Easy komt vanzelf naar de kant. De passagier stapt op het voetveer en vaart duurzaam en veilig naar de overkant. Volledig automatisch en zeer gemakkelijk. Het ontwerp van Ferry Easy zorgt er voor dat het voetveer onderhouds- en vandalismevrij is. Een camera aan boord zorgt mede voor de veiligheid van de passagiers.

Company description: Based in Ireland, SEA-Tech provides technical expertise to the Maritime and Agricultural Sectors. Highly specialised, we offer our clients tactical ICT consulting, technical professional services (integration), project management from inception to completion and technical support. Our solutions include primarily : Environmental data (IoT) with realtime delivery for weather stations and vision systems and any connected research scientific equipment. Wireless and cabled Marine data communication system providing:           • Seaport and Coastal high speed network wireless connectivity           • Self-contained, offshore private network (WMAN)           • Communications platforms for crews/passengers of visiting vessels.           • Bespoke applications e.g. boarding parties; naval operations; customs   Established in 2007, we have a reputation for excellence which has ensured our direct and continued involvement in a large number of public and private sector  projects. Our engineering power and consulting are the backbone of successfull projects. Dealing with top manufacturers like Lambrecht, Campbell Scientific, Davis Instruments, Orlaco, Hikvision, Mikrotik, Ubiquiti, PoE Texas and Victron we are also Rittal Ireland strategic partners for the marine industry in Ireland. Since 2013, SEA-Tech has developed its own cutting edge ship to shore data communication system. Able to hold a large bandwidth connection 15 nautical miles from the shore while a ship is evolving at top speeds, SeaFi solves a communication deficit for:           • Port authorities           • Naval Services & customs           • Commercial shipping & fishing           • Energy industry           • Ferry companies Since 2018, SeaFi holds the world record for the furthest maritime broadband transmission (no satellite or GSM) between a vessel offshore and a shore. This record was set to raise awareness on affordable alternative marine data-communication systems.

Company description: — Regenerative Ocean Mobility — Rethinking maritime mobility for resilient islands and living oceans. InSail is a regenerative maritime initiative based in the Canary Islands. We design and co-develop wind-powered vessels and strategic frameworks to transform how island territories connect—reducing environmental pressure while enhancing local sovereignty, biodiversity protection, and climate resilience. Our work goes far beyond decarbonization: it’s about building mobility systems that respect ecosystems, empower communities, and regenerate what has been harmed. Our Strategic Axes: We collaborate with shipyards, ferry operators, energy actors and hotel groups to co-develop wind-powered and circular mobility solutions tailored to island territories—designed for sustainable operations, long-term durability, and deep local integration. We also support island governments, international agencies, and conservation organizations with regenerative maritime strategies—feasibility studies, transition roadmaps, and turnkey pilots—focused on ecological balance, energy sovereignty, and territorial resilience. Education & Citizen Engagement: We foster ocean awareness and public participation through educational programs, scientific outreach, and collaborative storytelling initiatives. 💡 A regenerative model for high-value marine and island ecosystems From the Canary Islands to global ocean territories, we deliver “Impact-as-a-Service” tools and vessels adapted to the challenges of fragile archipelagos—merging innovation, engineering, science, and long-term vision. Let’s sail differently. Respectfully. Together.

Company description: Reederei Hiddensee, a shipping company subsidiary of the Weiße Flotte, was founded in 1995 to operate all the regular services from Zingst, Wiek, Stralsund and Schaprode to the island of Hiddensee. Through the establishment of Reederei Hiddensee the area of operations of the Weiße Flotte expanded to include ferry services (Glewitz - Stahlbrode, Warnemünde - Hohe Düne, Wittow Nord - Wittow-Süd) and excursions on the Baltic Sea. Weiße Flotte and Reederei Hiddensee carry annually 3.4 million passengers and 846,000 vehicles. Modern passenger vessels of the "Boddenkreuzer" type, a cargo ferry as well as fast water taxis make up the fleet that connects the island of Hiddensee with the island of Rügen all year round. During the summer months, connections from Stralsund, Wiek and Zingst are offered additionally. New or modernised passenger/car vessels are deployed for ferry services in Warnemünde (Hohe Düne), Wittower Fähre (Rügen) and Stahlbrode/Glewitz (Rügen). A large program of harbor trips complete the services offered.  Reederei Hiddensee is one of the ventures of the FRS Förde Reederei Seetouristik, an internationally business group base in Northern Germany with a portfolio that comprises twenty-one subsidiaries located in Europe, North Africa and North America. In addition to numerous international ferry and catamaran lines, a ship-management company and the operation of a port complete the product range.

Μέσω των δημοφιλών, εμπορικών σημάτων Superfast Ferries, Blue Star Ferries, Hellenic Seaways και ΑΝΕΚ Lines, με στόλο που αριθμεί πάνω από 40 πλοία και ανθρώπινο δυναμικό που ξεπερνά τους 2.500 εργαζομένους σε ξηρά και θάλασσα, συνδέει καθημερινά περισσότερους από 55 προορισμούς, προσφέροντας υψηλού επιπέδου μεταφορικές υπηρεσίες στην Ελλάδα και στις γραμμές εξωτερικού (Ελλάδα – Ιταλία). Τα τελευταία έτη, ο Όμιλος διευρύνει την παρουσία του στον τουριστικό τομέα, με την απόκτηση ξενοδοχειακών μονάδων στα νησιά της Τήνου (1) και της Νάξου (2) όπου δραστηριοποιείται, με στόχο την παροχή ολοκληρωμένων υπηρεσιών στους πελάτες του. Με σαφή δέσμευση για την ενσωμάτωση των αρχών της βιώσιμης ανάπτυξης σε όλο το φάσμα της επιχειρηματικής δραστηριότητας και των λειτουργιών της, η Attica Group αποτέλεσε την 1η εταιρεία στον κλάδο της επιβατηγού ναυτιλίας σε παγκόσμιο επίπεδο, που εξέδωσε Απολογισμό Υπεύθυνης και Βιώσιμης Ανάπτυξης το 2009, σύμφωνα με τις κατευθυντήριες οδηγίες GRI. 14 χρόνια μετά, η αξιολόγηση Standard & Poor’s Global Corporate Sustainability Assessment (CSA) 2023, κατατάσσει τον Όμιλο στο 25% των κορυφαίων εταιρειών παγκοσμίως για τον κλάδο Transportation Infrastructure.

Company description: The Irish Nautical Trust, along with The Dublin Port Company and Dublin City Council, are proud to bring the return of The Old Liffey Ferry Service to Dublin's Docklands. The Ferry service was first granted a charter in 1665 by King Charles II, (although there had been a ferry dating back at least to the 1400's), and it was eventually discontinued in 1984 with the opening of the then new East Link toll bridge (Tom Clarke Bridge). The Old Liffey Ferry service runs between the Cill Airne pontoon and Sir John Rogerson's Quay pontoon and The Point Depot (3Arena) pontoon, from 7am to 7pm - Monday to Friday, all year round.
